    {
      "sort": 200000,
      "name": "Night City Holdem: Gambling Rules For The Dark Future",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "UQdGYtuKTHpG5M8p",
      "title": {
        "show": false,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<h1>A High-Stakes Game Of Winner-Takes-All</h1><p>Gambling is as ubiquitous as ever in the Red Decades, as commonplace and widespread in the streets of Night City as crime and homelessness. Everything is played, from Texas Holdem to Liar's Dice, but a universal set of skills are applicable to basically any method of gambling you can think of.</p><h2>Start By Finding A Table</h2><p>Gamblers are everywhere in Night City, from street corners to gang hideouts to casinos and clubs. The difficulty of the table determines the number of rounds in each game/hand before it ends and players are able to cash out.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Easy opponents (3 rounds):</strong> street gangs, cube hotel poker tables</p></li><li><p><strong>Moderate opponents (6 rounds):</strong> casino tables, hobbyists, corporate poer tables</p></li><li><p><strong>Difficult opponents (9 rounds):</strong> career gamblers, high-stakes tournaments, etc.</p></li></ul><p>When you find a table, you're informed of the number of rounds and the ante is set by the GM, ranging from cash to gear to contract work. Any number of players can sit down at a table, though if the dealer smells collusion they'll be in for a swift kick in the ass.</p><h2>Running The Game/How To Win</h2><p>Each round consists of a facedown followed by 3 rolls (outlined below). To proceed to the next round, a player must pass 2/3 of the involved checks. If a player loses in the first third of the table's total rounds, they lose their ante to the table. If they lose in the second third, they break even. If they lose in the final third, they win back their ante + 50%. If the player doesn't lose, they double their ante.</p><h2>Face Down The Table (Start The Round)</h2><p>Before starting the round, you need to feel out your opponents. To do so, everyone in the game rolls a facedown check against the table DV (outlined below), the effect of which <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">always</span></span> and <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">only</span></span> concludes at the end of the round. If a palyer wins the facedown against the DV, they add 2 to their checks. If they lose the facedown, they subtract 2.</p><p>A player can choose to roll Gambling instead, against the same DV (the facedown doesn't happen, in this case). On success, they learn the round DV. On failure, nothing happens.</p><h2>Play A Hand (Rolls, DVs)</h2><p><strong>First,</strong> the GM determines the round DV by rolling a d10 and adding the number below. GMs can force the average instead, at their discretion. Players who passed their gambling check at the start of the round learn the DV; otherwise it is always kept secret.</p><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-table-overlap:never;mso-yfti-tbllook:1184;mso-table-lspace:9.0pt;margin-left:6.75pt;mso-table-rspace:9.0pt;margin-right:6.75pt;mso-table-anchor-vertical:paragraph;mso-table-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-table-left:right;mso-table-top:-.3pt;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;mso-border-insideh:none;mso-border-insidev:1.0pt solid windowtext\"><tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:58.5pt;border:none;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><h3 style=\"margin-bottom:0in;text-align:center;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:paragraph;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:right;mso-element-top:-.3pt;mso-height-rule:exactly\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-fareast-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-ansi-language:EN\">Round #</span></h3></td><td style=\"width:31.5pt;border:none;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><h3 style=\"margin-bottom:0in;tex