ght;mso-element-top:-.3pt;mso-height-rule:exactly;text-align:center\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-ansi-language:EN\">18</span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:9;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes\"><td style=\"width:58.5pt;border:none;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:paragraph;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:right;mso-element-top:-.3pt;mso-height-rule:exactly;text-align:center\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-ansi-language:EN\">9</span></p></td><td style=\"width:31.5pt;border:none;border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:paragraph;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:right;mso-element-top:-.3pt;mso-height-rule:exactly;text-align:center\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-ansi-language:EN\">15</span></p></td><td style=\"width:.5in;border:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;mso-element:frame;mso-element-frame-hspace:9.0pt;mso-element-wrap:around;mso-element-anchor-vertical:paragraph;mso-element-anchor-horizontal:margin;mso-element-left:right;mso-element-top:-.3pt;mso-height-rule:exactly;text-align:center\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-bidi-font-family:'Times New Roman';mso-ansi-language:EN\">24</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Next,</strong> each player gets a turn action which they can use at any point in the round. These actions can be used to help with their next roll, or be made towards other ends.</p><p><strong>Finally,</strong> each player makes a series of 3 checks against the determined DV. Checks within a round always follow the same sequence. Each player must beat 2 checks, or they lose the round. See the previous section for what happens when they lose, based on how many rounds the table has and how far they got.</p><ul><li><p><strong>1 – The Human Element:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">EMP+Human Perception</span></span> (interact with your opponent) or <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">WILL+Concentration</span></span> (keep your composure)</p></li><li><p><strong>2 – The Game Itself:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">INT+Gamble</span></span> (count cards, etc.) or <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">COOL+Forgery or TECH+Forgery</span></span> (fake out your opponent)</p></li><li><p><strong>3 –</strong> <strong>Luck Save:</strong> Roll 1d10; a result which is ≤ the character's LUCK stat is considered a pass (use 1/2 Lowndown for mooks, to a max of 8).</p></li></ul><h2>End The Round</h2><p>Once players have concluded all their rolls, the round ends; facedowns fade, losers leave the table, and the next round begins. If no players and/or no rounds remain, the game ends.</p>"
